>     Hell Beast pointed over to the alcove where the computers for 
the engins, 
> enviormental controls, and such, were located. "He's there. Im sure 
you two 
> will get along nicely."
> 
>     Megatron moved onward, this time with a quickened pace. The 
bridge was 2 
> levels above them now. Because the lock down was in place, it would 
be near 
> impossible to get into any of the rooms. The corridor doors could 
be forced 
> open, but it took time. As for the shields, Megatron made sure that 
he was 
> closing a path behinde him, and opening a path before him. In case 
they did 
> stumble across the rebels, all he had to do was raise a shield. Of 
course, 
> being an internal shield it would last only 10 minutes of crossfire 
before it 
> gave way. Plenty of time in Megatrons mind to either stand ground 
or retreat.
>     "Were almost thier. Nothing to worry about." Rampage said, his 
large 
> triple missle launcher cast over his shoulder.
